<br>
I do think that if you choose the realitive safety of a zone line camp that you have to accept as part of the reward that you might get trained but then that is why you are by the zone right so you can yourself zone easily if need be?  If people camping the zone were more sure of themselves they would be deeper in most likely in a safer camp that is less likely to get trained.  Therefore they are not just innocent bystanders.  <br>
<br>
I expect anyone crossing a street to stop and look before they step out into the line of traffic.  That is why I teach my children to stop and look both ways for cars and to only proceed into the street if there are no cars coming.  Just last year I had my son run in front of a car Thank God the person driving was able to stop.  However had they not been able to stop it would have been my and my sons fault, mine for not seeing as he ran out even though I was right there and  his for not looking at all.  <br>
 <p>

Evelle Dark Priestess of Inny

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughiastormwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghia Stormwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:28:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re. EverQuest Law</span><hr size=1> And in that split second that I saw him dashing in front of the car he totally didn't see and seeing how fast the car was going through my mind flashed his short life and how I was going be holding his broken body.  In that second in my mind he has already died.  In that same time I already felt the pain of the person driving (a little too fast honestly) I knew the horror they must have felt as they saw his tiny body run in front of them and I didn't feel hatred for them I felt compassion.  I knew they would have to live with his death just as I did only for them they wouldn't have had all the sweet memories of his life just the tragic last few seconds.  But I do accept my responsiblity when it comes to things they put my life and the life of my family at risk.  <br>
<br>
Just like in EQ I accept responsiblity for sitting on a zone line as a choice I made due to the relative safety it implied.<br>
<br>
I am very thankful that on that night that person was able to stop.  <p>

Evelle Dark Priestess of Inny

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucnjmorris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cnjmorris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:32:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re. EverQuest Law</span><hr size=1> Ghia,<br>
<br>
Like I said, all zones are different.  I was talking ONLY about KC.  <br>
<br>
Zone into mistmore at level 25 and get wiped, fine.. its the zone, you expect it.  Zone into befallen at level 16 and get wiped, fine.. its the zone, you expect it.<br>
<br>
Yes, left side KC is a zone too... but so is right.  In most zones there is no choice, you run, you save your life.  KC offers a choice AND neither is farther than the other.<br>
<br>
I can not think of any reason to go left instead of right.  If I was zoning out and there was a group on the right and none on the left... I would still go right.  I would then politely tell them that it is accepted tactic in KC to always zone right and that they may have better luck on the left.<br>
<br>
