<br>
I am not a part of people making trains in KC ever.  I am just a part of people that don't like to listen to people whine when it happens. <p>

Evelle Dark Priestess of Inny

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucnjmorris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cnjmorris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:57:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re. EverQuest Law</span><hr size=1> Ghia,<br>
<br>
Everyone makes trains.  I wasn't meaning to imply you make more than your share, or that you do it intentionally.  When I say &quot;you&quot; I am refering to anyone training, including myself.<br>
<br>
My point is that if and when trains happen in KC, and I am ONLY refering to KC, what possible reason is there not to zone right?<br>
<br>
I am not whining, I am asking why.  I think I have hunted in KC once since I was trained on zone in.  Once, so this isn't even about me.<br>
<br>
You can sit there and say people shouldn't sit at zone, but then again, why are they stupid enough to hunt in KC in the first place?<br>
<br>
Trains will happen.  People will get aggro.  People shouldn't sit at zones and expect to live.  People shouldn't start trains.  These aren't questions.  There is one question being discussed here really and that is why won't people just train right? <p><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~cnjmorris/catcen.jpg>

